  assumptions: [
    { id:'AR01', topic:'QR Code Content', statement:'The QR code in the Roller confirmation email encodes a Booking ID, not a Ticket ID or Custom Ticket ID.', status:'Needs verification', whyItMatters:'Roller Mobile Check-in docs confirm that scanning a Booking ID does not trigger automatic redemption. If QR = Booking ID, JY Cloud must first call GET booking to resolve Ticket IDs before redemption can proceed.', sourceUrl:'https://mysupport.roller.software/hc/en-us/articles/6411196568079-Search-for-and-redeem-tickets-using-the-Mobile-Check-in-app', sourceLabel:'Roller: Mobile Check-in - ticket ID vs booking ID' },
    { id:'AR02', topic:'REST Redeem Endpoint for Self-Service', statement:'The public Roller REST "Redeem tickets" endpoint can be used for production self-service check-in without a staffed POS device.', status:'Needs verification', whyItMatters:'The endpoint is documented and confirmed to exist. However, the Roller API FAQ states that the onboarding package is intended to assess use-case feasibility with a Roller technical expert. Production suitability for unmanned self-service must be confirmed before sprint 2 development begins.', sourceUrl:'https://mysupport.roller.software/hc/en-us/articles/360003171476-ROLLER-API-FAQ', sourceLabel:'Roller API FAQ' },
    { id:'AR03', topic:'Booking ID to Ticket ID Resolution', statement:'JumpYard Cloud must resolve the scanned Booking ID to one or more Ticket IDs via GET booking detail before calling the Redeem tickets endpoint.', status:'Assumption', whyItMatters:'Roller REST: Redeem tickets endpoint operates at ticket level. Booking ID alone cannot drive redemption. JY Cloud is the resolution layer. If Roller changes the QR to encode Ticket IDs directly, this step could be simplified.', sourceUrl:'https://docs.roller.app/docs/rest-api/fb1d84952285f', sourceLabel:'Roller REST: Redeem tickets' },
    { id:'AR04', topic:'Ticket-Level vs Booking-Level Check-in State', statement:'Roller tracks check-in as ticket redemption state (redemptions_used, redeemed_ticket_ids, redeem_date), not as a generic booking-level checked_in boolean.', status:'Needs verification', whyItMatters:'This is the difference between "has someone from this booking entered" (booking-level) and "which specific tickets have been redeemed" (ticket-level). The architecture and attendance reporting depend on this distinction.', sourceUrl:'https://docs.roller.app/docs/rest-api/fb1d84952285f', sourceLabel:'Roller REST: Redeem tickets' },
    { id:'AR05', topic:'Partial Group Check-in', statement:'A guest booking for 4 people may arrive in two separate groups at different times. Each group checks in against the same booking_id, redeeming a subset of ticket_ids each time.', status:'Needs verification', whyItMatters:'If Roller allows redemption of a subset of tickets from one booking, partial group self-service check-in is feasible. If not, partial groups must always be handled by staff. This affects the kiosk UI and JY Cloud logic significantly.', sourceUrl:null, sourceLabel:null },
    { id:'AR06', topic:'Unpaid Booking Handling at Kiosk (v1)', statement:"If a booking's payment_status is unpaid at check-in time, the v1 kiosk will route the guest to staff for payment collection. The kiosk will not process payment.", status:'Assumption', whyItMatters:'Sets scope boundary for v1 kiosk. Unpaid handling could be a future kiosk payment flow.', sourceUrl:null, sourceLabel:null },
    { id:'AR07', topic:'OAuth2 Token Management', statement:'JumpYard Cloud maintains a reusable OAuth2 access token for Roller API calls. Tokens are not requested per API call. Credentials are scoped to a single venue.', status:'Confirmed', whyItMatters:'Roller API overview explicitly states tokens should be reused. Per-call token requests would fail under load and consume rate limit budget. JY Cloud must implement token lifecycle management.', sourceUrl:'https://mysupport.roller.software/hc/en-us/articles/360001653455-API-overview', sourceLabel:'Roller API overview' },
    { id:'AR08', topic:'Roller API Rate Limit', statement:'Roller imposes a rate limit of one API call per second per credential set.', status:'Confirmed', whyItMatters:'At peak entry periods (for example session start times) many guests may arrive simultaneously. JY Cloud must implement a queue or throttle to stay within the 1 call/sec limit. Burst scenarios at kiosk must be designed for.', sourceUrl:'https://mysupport.roller.software/hc/en-us/articles/360001653455-API-overview', sourceLabel:'Roller API overview' },
    { id:'AR09', topic:'Webhook Events Post-Redemption', statement:'Roller webhooks may fire events after a ticket is redeemed, enabling JY Cloud to receive a push notification of the state change rather than polling.', status:'Needs verification', whyItMatters:'Webhook support post-redemption would enable reactive JY Cloud event handling, reduce polling, and improve reliability. The webhook endpoint is documented but specific event types for ticket redemption must be confirmed.', sourceUrl:'https://docs.roller.app/docs/rest-api/ebd73c57a6e38-view-webhooks', sourceLabel:'Roller REST: View webhooks' },
    { id:'AR10', topic:'Capacity / Session Slot Reserved at Booking', statement:'Roller reserves the session slot capacity at the time of booking, before the guest arrives.', status:'Assumption', whyItMatters:'If capacity is not reserved at booking time, double-booking scenarios are possible. The current capacity model affects future kiosk validation logic.', sourceUrl:null, sourceLabel:null },
    { id:'AR11', topic:'Attendance Report Impact', statement:'Ticket redemptions performed via REST API are reflected in Roller Attendance Reports.', status:'Needs verification', whyItMatters:'If API-driven redemptions do not appear in attendance reports, JumpYard loses operational visibility. Confirmed for POS-driven redemptions; REST API equivalence must be verified.', sourceUrl:'https://mysupport.roller.software/hc/en-us/articles/11953623976847-Attendance-report', sourceLabel:'Roller: Attendance report' }
  ],
